column1: purpose: to see why we are getting slower uptake of CO than previously comparing different growth media and 1YCM to see if salt solution messed everything up
only use black caps for everything!!!
The rinse step will all be with xtra cys
Tubes C,F,I, & K flushed w/ argon for 2 minutes
All other tubes were place in larger 1L bottles and those bottles were flushed for 10minutes each with argon.
All tubes placed in anaerobic chamber at 1:30.
Tubes A,B,C and G,H,I were rehydrated w/ 4mL of 1YCM with xtra cys and Na2S
Tubes D,E,F and J,K,L were rehydrated w/ 4mL of 1YCM with xtra cys
All tubes flushed with syngas for 2min at 10psi
All tubes placed in shaker at 2pm.

The humidity sensors that were placed in conditions similar to the samples above returned expected results. The drierite and flushed conditions showed no change in humidity, while the LiCl sensor appeared slightly pinker.
**Note: after the first assay the tubes were stored such that some papers were submerged under the media affecting the CO uptake.
